Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.02,0:01:01.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家好\N{\fs90}Hello, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.02,0:01:04.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\fs90}Hello! Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.53,0:01:10.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家好\N{\fs90}Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.87,0:01:13.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢大家\N{\fs90}Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.84,0:01:17.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,真热情啊\N{\fs90}What a welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.14,0:01:19.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家好 非常感谢\N{\fs90}Hello. Thank you, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.57,0:01:21.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到The Grand Tour\N{\fs90}Welcome to The Grand Tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.74,0:01:25.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,这次我们来到了尼斯湖畔\N{\fs90}which this week comes to you from the shores of Loch Ness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.17,0:01:27.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,在苏格兰\N{\fs90}in Scotland!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.78,0:01:29.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在\N{\fs90}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.05,0:01:31.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\fs90}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.37,0:01:33.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 对于世界上大多数人而言\N{\fs90}Now, to most people around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.16,0:01:35.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,苏格兰只是一堆美景\N{\fs90}Scotland is just a bunch of scenery
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.72,0:01:38.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有脸上画着颜料的梅尔吉布森\N{\fs90}and Mel Gibson with some paint on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.71,0:01:40.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,但实际上不止这些\N{\fs90}But actually it's a bit more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:44.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里有一张表 记录了在美国发明的\N{\fs90}What we have here is a list of all the important things
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.17,0:01:46.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有重要的东西\N{\fs90}that were invented in America, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.17,0:01:48.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,德国发明了这些\N{\fs90}This is what the Germans came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.08,0:01:51.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里是英国的贡献\N{\fs90}Then we've got the English contribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.42,0:01:54.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,再看看法国人做了些什么\N{\fs90}And then let's have a look at what France did.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.41,0:01:58.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这样 我没瞎编\N{\fs90}That's it. I'm not making that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.98,0:02:00.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实还有卷笔刀\N{\fs90}Actually and the pencil sharpener.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.18,0:02:01.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦还有卷笔刀\N{\fs90}Oh, and the pencil sharpener!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.72,0:02:04.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我们看看\N{\fs90}Now let's have a look at the list of things
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.72,0:02:07.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,苏格兰人发明的东西\N{\fs90}that were invented by Scottish people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.46,0:02:09.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,这简直是\N{\fs90}It's just...!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.59,0:02:13.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,不可思议 囊括世间万物\N{\fs90}It's unbelievable! It's everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.70,0:02:17.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,无烟火药 克隆技术 彩色相片\N{\fs90}Cordite. Cloning. Colour photography.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.63,0:02:19.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,雷管\N{\fs90}Percussion cap.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.53,0:02:22.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,高尔夫 浓缩柠檬汁 数不胜数\N{\fs90}Golf, lime cordial. I mean, the list goes on and on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.37,0:02:25.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,-别克 -等等\N{\fs90}- Buick! - Hang on a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.37,0:02:27.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,为啥美国海军也算\N{\fs90}Why is the US Navy on there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.02,0:02:31.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,讲真 那还真是一个苏格兰人发明的\N{\fs90}Not joking, that was actually invented by a Scottish person.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.94,0:02:34.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是吗 -BBC也是 英国特种空勤团也是\N{\fs90}- Was it? - So was the BBC, so was the SAS.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.45,0:02:37.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有的特种部队都是 我知道为什么\N{\fs90}All Special Forces, in fact. And I think I know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.65,0:02:41.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你来自墨西哥法国或者意大利\N{\fs90}If you are from Mexico or France or Italy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.34,0:02:42.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,早上醒来 拉开窗帘\N{\fs90}you wake up in the morning, open the curtains,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.62,0:02:44.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,天气晴朗 你就想 我要去海滩\N{\fs90}it's a lovely day, think, "I'll go to the beach."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.06,0:02:47.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,在苏格兰你拉开窗帘\N{\fs90}In Scotland you open the curtains...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.83,0:02:49.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,外面又湿又冷\N{\fs90}it's damp and cold:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.46,0:02:51.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,就会想 我要去棚子里造点什么\N{\fs90}"I'll go to the shed and I'll invent something."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.67,0:02:53.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际情况就是这样\N{\fs90}That's what's going on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.74,0:02:56.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实上我很惊讶 英国人\N{\fs90}I'm surprised, actually, the English,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.07,0:02:59.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,从来不说这是不列颠的发明\N{\fs90}don't just say that those are British inventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.14,0:03:01.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 这是安迪穆雷综合症\N{\fs90}Ah, yes, the Andy Murray syndrome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.25,0:03:04.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,说实话 这经常发生\N{\fs90}Let's be honest, this does happen a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.98,0:03:06.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 亚历山大格雷汉姆贝尔\N{\fs90}OK. Alexander Graham Bell,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.01,0:03:08.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,当他在他的小屋里\N{\fs90}when he was working away
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.65,0:03:10.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,捣鼓他的胶木电话和电线时\N{\fs90}with his Bakelite and his wires in his shed,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.59,0:03:12.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,他是个苏格兰疯子\N{\fs90}he was a Scottish crackpot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:15.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,但他发明了电话以后\N{\fs90}When he invented the telephone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.39,0:03:17.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就变成不列颠天才了\N{\fs90}he was a British genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:20.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,运动领域也有这种情况\N{\fs90}Exactly the same sort of thing happens with sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.33,0:03:22.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,搞赛车的杰基斯图尔特\N{\fs90}Motor racing, Jackie Stewart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.43,0:03:25.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,三次F1世界冠军\N{\fs90}Three times Formula 1 World Champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.37,0:03:26.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 他是英国人\N{\fs90}OK, he's British.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.60,0:03:30.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,吉姆克拉克 两次F1世界冠军 英国人\N{\fs90}Jim Clark. Two times Formula 1 World Champion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:33.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,大卫库特哈德 苏格兰人\N{\fs90}British. David Coulthard... Scottish.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.28,0:03:39.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这个道理\N{\fs90}That's how it works!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:42.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -我们应该向美国观众\N{\fs90}- It is, yes. - Maybe we should explain
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.14,0:03:44.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,解释一下发生了什么\N{\fs90}to people in America what's going on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.17,0:03:45.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,对的 我来帮你们理清楚\N{\fs90}Yeah, exactly. Let me just clear this up for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.05,0:03:47.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,大西洋彼岸的规矩是这样的\N{\fs90}This is how it works on this side of the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:50.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是大英帝国 这里是英格兰 我们老家\N{\fs90}This is Britain. This bit is England, where we're from.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.79,0:03:52.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是苏格兰 我们现在的位置\N{\fs90}This bit's Scotland, where we are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.82,0:03:55.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,这部分是威尔士 在我家旁边\N{\fs90}This bit's Wales, which is next to where I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.94,0:03:58.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,很好 规矩很简单\N{\fs90}Exactly. The rules are very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:03:59.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你是英格兰人\N{\fs90}If you're English
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.94,0:04:02.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,当你功成名就的时候\N{\fs90}and you become brilliant or do something brilliant,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.45,0:04:03.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,你还是英格兰人\N{\fs90}you remain English.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.67,0:04:05.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你是苏格兰人或者威尔士人\N{\fs90}If you're Scottish or Welsh
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.31,0:04:07.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,一旦你功成名就了\N{\fs90}and you do something brilliant,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.17,0:04:11.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,英格兰就认定你是不列颠人了\N{\fs90}the English decide that you are, in fact, British.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.01,0:04:14.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,英格兰人真是坏透了 不是吗\N{\fs90}The English really are appalling, aren't they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.71,0:04:16.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是的\N{\fs90}They are!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.96,0:04:23.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,我告诉你们 我喜欢待在苏格兰\N{\fs90}I tell you what, I love being in Scotland
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.33,0:04:25.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为所有人都直抒胸臆\N{\fs90}because everyone here speaks their mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:27.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有什么模棱两可\N{\fs90}There's no ambiguity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.70,0:04:30.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,苏格兰小镇拉克霍尔 他们的欢迎标语\N{\fs90}The town of Larkhall in Scotland, their welcome sign,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.65,0:04:32.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们来看\N{\fs90}here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:41.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是苏格兰\N{\fs90}This is Scotland.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.11,0:04:43.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,不只是说说 他们还付诸行动\N{\fs90}It's not just words, either, it's actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.35,0:04:45.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,还记得几年前格拉斯哥机场的\N{\fs90}Do you remember that terrorist attack at Glasgow Airport
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:47.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,恐怖袭击吗\N{\fs90}a couple of years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:49.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,有人想自爆 但炸弹没炸\N{\fs90}Somebody tried to explode... bomb didn't go off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.98,0:04:51.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就跑了 但没跑多远\N{\fs90}He ran off and he didn't get very far
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.69,0:04:54.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为发生了这件事 \N{\fs90}because this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.43,0:05:02.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,苏格兰人的处世方式\N{\fs90}The Scottish way. That is the Scottish way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.23,0:05:06.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有\N{\fs90}And um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.67,0:05:10.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,有趣的是 自此苏格兰再也没有恐怖袭击了\N{\fs90}Interestingly, there have been no terrorist attacks in Scotland since.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.45,0:05:12.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,好好想一想\N{\fs90}Just thinking about that for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:14.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,当他踢他的时候 他的脚一定是撞断\N{\fs90}When he kicked him, he must have broken his foot
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.18,0:05:15.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,在另一个人的骨盆上了\N{\fs90}on the other guy's pelvis.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:18.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是啊 -这说明那人的蛋蛋\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - Which means the guy's plums
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:20.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在冲击的中心区域\N{\fs90}were in the middle of the impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.78,0:05:24.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,当恐怖分子那天早上醒来时\N{\fs90}When that terrorist woke up that morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.42,0:05:25.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,他肯定想 好吧\N{\fs90}he must've thought, "Right,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.89,0:05:27.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天我将遇到的最糟糕的事\N{\fs90}"The worst thing that'll happen to me today
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.06,0:05:29.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是我要炸了\N{\fs90}is I'm gonna blow up."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:30.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这并不是最糟的 不是吗\N{\fs90}It wasn't, though, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.79,0:05:33.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为唯一爆掉的东西是他的蛋蛋\N{\fs90}Cos the only thing to explode was his knackers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.90,0:05:36.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们能继续了吗 -好主意\N{\fs90}- Can we get on with the show? - Yes. Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.43,0:05:39.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为在今晚的汽车节目中\N{\fs90}Because in tonight's car programme...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.40,0:05:42.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在发动机上尿尿\N{\fs90}I urinate on an engine...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.57,0:05:45.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德穿了件滑雪衫\N{\fs90}Richard wears an anorak...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.61,0:05:49.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长磕了药\N{\fs90}and James takes drugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.85,0:05:53.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,但首先 我想聊一下菲亚特\N{\fs90}But first, I want to talk about Fiat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.05,0:05:56.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在最有名的是菲亚特500\N{\fs90}They're mostly known these days for the 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.15,0:05:57.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,一辆复古的小掀背车\N{\fs90}which is a small retro hatchback.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.05,0:06:00.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是缺席了数十年后\N{\fs90}But after an absence of more than a decade,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.25,0:06:02.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们又回到了赛车场上\N{\fs90}they are back in the sports car game.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.71,0:06:04.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我去了埃博拉症赛道\N{\fs90}So I went down to the Eboladrome
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:05.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看他们拿出了什么\N{\fs90}to check out what they've come up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.67,0:06:23.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是它了 对比下500\N{\fs90}Here it is. And as with the 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.48,0:06:24.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以立马看出\N{\fs90}you can tell straightaway
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.88,0:06:28.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,菲亚特打了怀旧牌\N{\fs90}that Fiat are playing the nostalgia card
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.48,0:06:32.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这辆车叫做124 Spider\N{\fs90}because this car is called the 124 Spider,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.45,0:06:37.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,向70年代的后驱双座跑车致敬\N{\fs90}in honour of their rear-wheel drive roadster from the '70s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而在外表之下\N{\fs90}Under the skin, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.86,0:06:45.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,124基于全新的马自达MX-5\N{\fs90}the 124 is based on the thoroughly modern Mazda MX-5.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.23,0:06:49.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,菲亚特提供了一些重要的部件 例如引擎\N{\fs90}Fiat supply some important things like the engine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.11,0:06:50.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有车身\N{\fs90}and the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.37,0:06:51.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这两辆车都是\N{\fs90}but both cars are built
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.80,0:06:54.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,在日本的同一生产线上制造的\N{\fs90}on the same production line in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.14,0:06:58.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,从表面上看 没有什么问题\N{\fs90}On the surface, that is no bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:00.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,你晚上能睡得更安稳\N{\fs90}You're gonna sleep a lot better at night
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.88,0:07:02.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为知道你的意大利车\N{\fs90}knowing that your Italian car
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.22,0:07:05.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上是日本人组装的\N{\fs90}was actually put together by the Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.12,0:07:07.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这也产生了一个问题\N{\fs90}However, it does raise a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.92,0:07:10.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是菲亚特自己的跑车\N{\fs90}Is that a sports car in its own right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:13.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,还是一辆贴牌的马自达\N{\fs90}or just a Mazda with a different badge on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.93,0:07:16.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 在我们探寻之前\N{\fs90}Well, before we find out,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.83,0:07:19.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们近距离看一下这个标志\N{\fs90}let's look a bit more closely at the badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.10,0:07:22.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你会注意到 上面写着阿巴斯\N{\fs90}Because you'll notice it says Abarth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.54,0:07:26.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,当菲亚特想要在车底点一把火的时候\N{\fs90}Abarth are Fiat's go-to people
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.94,0:07:30.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿巴斯就是他们的关键人物\N{\fs90}when they want to light a fire under one of their cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.24,0:07:34.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是真点一把火 而是在已有的基础上\N{\fs90}Not light an actual fire, but give what's already there
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.42,0:07:38.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,添加一些热情 活力 还有火\N{\fs90}some extra zest and zing and fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.86,0:07:45.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先 阿巴斯调校了1.4升涡轮增压发动机\N{\fs90}For starters, Abarth has tuned the 1.4 litre turbo-charged engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.91,0:07:50.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以这最火热的124 比任何MX-5都快\N{\fs90}so that this, the hottest 124, is faster than any MX- 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.30,0:07:56.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,百公里加速6.8秒\N{\fs90}0- 60 takes 6.8 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:03.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,最高时速233公里\N{\fs90}And the top speed is 145mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.14,0:08:07.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,但在这样的车里感觉时速有233百万\N{\fs90}But in a car like this that feels like 145 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.82,0:08:11.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,对我而言肯定够了\N{\fs90}Certainly bundles for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.96,0:08:17.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,124不仅是性能上远远超过了\N{\fs90}And it's not just performance where the 124 has the edge
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.51,0:08:20.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,他同父异母的日本兄弟\N{\fs90}over its Japanese half-brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.93,0:08:22.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,我必须承认 这还是一个\N{\fs90}I have to admit, and this comes from someone
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.90,0:08:26.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,在MX-5上挑不出毛病的人说的\N{\fs90}who struggles to find fault with the MX-5,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:29.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,124的声音更棒\N{\fs90}the 124 does sound better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.71,0:08:36.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿巴斯安装了 Record Monza 排气系统\N{\fs90}Abarth have given it something called the Record Monza exhaust system.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.34,0:08:41.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能让小车发出大车的噪声\N{\fs90}What it does is make a small car produce a big-car noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:52.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像披着狮子皮的猫\N{\fs90}It's like a cat in a lion suit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.34,0:08:54.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是你想要的戏剧效果\N{\fs90}and that's exactly the sort of panto you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.43,0:08:59.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想说的是 这车我行我素\N{\fs90}What I'm saying here is that this car does its own thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.74,0:09:02.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,它有自己的个性 那很重要\N{\fs90}It has its own personality. And that's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.74,0:09:08.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,但接下来的一点 可是124的软肋\N{\fs90}But on the next point, the 124 does take a bit of a body blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.68,0:09:16.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 这辆阿巴斯很贵\N{\fs90}You see, there's a price to pay for all this Abarth-ness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.38,0:09:19.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,价格是30000英镑\N{\fs90}And that price is ￡30,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.02,0:09:23.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,比顶配MX-5要多5000英镑\N{\fs90}￡5,000 more than the top MX-5.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.63,0:09:28.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过 124在皮囊之下给的东西更多\N{\fs90}That said, the 124 does give you more under the skin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.53,0:09:33.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,特别是在操控系统上\N{\fs90}most notably in the handling department.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.40,0:09:38.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿巴斯给车配备了一个限滑差速器\N{\fs90}The thing is, Abarth have given this car a limited-slip diff...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.21,0:09:41.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,这让漂移变得信手拈来\N{\fs90}which makes sliding something you command.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:52.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,MX-5可没有这个\N{\fs90}The MX-5 doesn't have that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.85,0:09:55.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,也没有这个运动模式按钮\N{\fs90}Neither does it have this sport button here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.66,0:09:58.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能将稳定控制系统放开\N{\fs90}which relaxes the stability control.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:00.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,放得非常开\N{\fs90}Quite a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.34,0:10:15.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 我们有一辆很快的车\N{\fs90}So, what we have here is a car that's fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.58,0:10:18.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,它声浪迷人 过弯富有乐趣\N{\fs90}sounds good and is great fun in the corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:25.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,但还有更重要的一点\N{\fs90}But there's something else very important about the 124.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.26,0:10:31.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不知道它和MX-5是不是真的\N{\fs90}I don't know that there's really a million miles of difference
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.94,0:10:33.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,差了十万八千里\N{\fs90}between this and the MX-5.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.37,0:10:40.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,但当我开这车时 我开的是辆意大利跑车\N{\fs90}But everything I do in this car I'm doing in an Italian sports car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.60,0:10:46.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不可能让你提不起兴致\N{\fs90}And it is impossible for that not to put you in a good mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.41,0:10:52.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,再次坐进一辆意大利双座小跑车的感觉真好\N{\fs90}It does feel so good to be in a small, Italian roadster again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.97,0:10:55.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,也该是时候了\N{\fs90}It's about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:11:00.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆小菲亚特就是要搅动你的情绪\N{\fs90}Everything about this little Fiat is designed to stir the emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.57,0:11:02.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,让你笑得像个孩子\N{\fs90}And make you smile like a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.99,0:11:05.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,直至这个黑色复古引擎盖\N{\fs90}Right down to the retro black bonnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.86,0:11:08.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,天呐 我爱黑色的引擎盖\N{\fs90}God, I love a black bonnet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.23,0:11:10.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,这实在是\N{\fs90}It just... Ooh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.73,0:11:12.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这简直是 一个黑色的引擎盖\N{\fs90}It's just...a black bonnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.80,0:11:16.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,只有酷的车才有黑色前盖 真的\N{\fs90}Only cool cars have black bonnets. Fact!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.94,0:11:19.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,我很喜欢MX-5\N{\fs90}I really like the MX-5.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.57,0:11:23.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,但124在日式的基础上\N{\fs90}But the 124 has taken those Japanese foundations
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.18,0:11:25.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,又加入了些意式的表演技巧\N{\fs90}and added some Italian showmanship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.88,0:11:30.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以比起马自达我更想要这个\N{\fs90}That's why I'd have it over the Mazda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.79,0:11:33.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不只是喜欢它 我爱它\N{\fs90}I don't just like it, I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.76,0:11:44.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很有趣 因为\N{\fs90}It's interesting that, because...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.13,0:11:47.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道 我热衷于意大利跑车\N{\fs90}..as you know, I'm a sucker for an Italian sports car.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.77,0:11:50.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,爱之入骨 尤其是阿尔法\N{\fs90}Love'em to bits especially the Alfa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.54,0:11:54.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而 我开过普通版的124\N{\fs90}However, I've driven an ordinary, cooking Fiat 124
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.42,0:11:58.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有MX-5那么好 难以望其项背\N{\fs90}and that is not as good as an MX-5, not even close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.05,0:12:00.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,对的 你还是不要MX-5了\N{\fs90}That's true. You'd be better off with the MX-5.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:02.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,除非你想要最快的MX-5\N{\fs90}Unless you want the fastest MX-5,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.78,0:12:04.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就是买一辆阿巴斯\N{\fs90}in which case buy the Abarth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.71,0:12:08.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,-很有道理 -我们是不是给了消费者建议\N{\fs90}- Quite. - Have we just done consumer advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.89,0:12:11.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一点 我们快速过\N{\fs90}A little bit. A little bit. Moving on quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:13.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 我们继续 我们来看看\N{\fs90}Yes, we will, move it on. And we'll find out
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:16.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿巴斯在埃博拉症赛道上能跑多快\N{\fs90}how fast the Abarth goes round the Eboladrome.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:18.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然了 那就意味着将他交给\N{\fs90}That, of course, means handing it over to a man
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.17,0:12:20.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,一个认为胡子是列宁发明的人\N{\fs90}who thinks that beards were invented by Lenin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.00,0:12:24.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 就是老美\N{\fs90}Yep. It's the American.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.31,0:12:26.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,他来了 从容不迫 蓄势待发\N{\fs90}There he is, poised and ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.97,0:12:28.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,他出发了\N{\fs90}And he's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.04,0:12:30.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,轮胎轻微打滑\N{\fs90}With a skitter of wheelspin
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.01,0:12:32.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,排气声圆滑悦耳\N{\fs90}and a fruity noise from the exhaust.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.65,0:12:37.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,直接进入湿漉漉的不直道\N{\fs90}Straight onto a soaking-wet Isn't Strait.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.68,0:12:39.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的生活...\N{\fs90}What the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.02,0:12:42.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,到底经历了什么...\N{\fs90}has happened in my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.06,0:12:45.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,我才会在湿乎乎的英国...\N{\fs90}that I'm over here driving a Fiat...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.56,0:12:48.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,开一辆菲亚特\N{\fs90}in the wet in England?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.56,0:12:52.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,也许他并不乐在其中 但他的确精于此道\N{\fs90}He may not be enjoying it but he is very good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.13,0:12:55.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,他驾驶着124飞快掠过积水\N{\fs90}As he carves the 124 through the standing water,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:59.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,将这170匹马力发挥得淋漓尽致\N{\fs90}making the best use of its 170 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.84,0:13:03.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,通过留你名弯 车身倾斜得很厉害啊\N{\fs90}Really leaning on it as he approaches Your Name Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.31,0:13:04.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,真是大胆\N{\fs90}That is ballsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.85,0:13:06.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 大脚刹车\N{\fs90}Now, heavy on the brakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.48,0:13:09.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,紧凑而快速地通过这个左弯\N{\fs90}swoops round this fast left-hander,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.42,0:13:13.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,极富技巧 优雅又慌乱地转向过度出弯\N{\fs90}and exits with a skilful flurry of stylish over-steer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.49,0:13:15.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到不直道\N{\fs90}Back onto the Isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.22,0:13:17.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,见鬼 我都不知道这车到底是拿来开的\N{\fs90}Hell, I don't know whether to drive this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:19.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,还是拿来当漱口杯的\N{\fs90}or use it for a spit-cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:21.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,好极了\N{\fs90}Charming!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.00,0:13:23.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,呆子们会觉得\N{\fs90}Nerds will note these conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.33,0:13:25.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,Barchetta会更符合这些条件\N{\fs90}would be better suited to a Barchetta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.87,0:13:27.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你喜欢这辆车的话\N{\fs90}If you like this car,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.50,0:13:30.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,我打赌你家里肯定有一堆花里胡哨的靠垫\N{\fs90}I bet you got a lot of fancy cushions in your house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:32.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 因为我们都知道\N{\fs90}Yeah, cos as we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.34,0:13:34.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,靠垫当然代表着 我党\N{\fs90}cushions are, of course, Communist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.38,0:13:39.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 进入老奶房狭窄的弯角\N{\fs90}Right, into the tight complex of Old Lady's House.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.18,0:13:41.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,紧凑而完美的通过了\N{\fs90}Keeping it nice and tidy through there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.52,0:13:45.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,全油门通过坑坑洼洼的不平路\N{\fs90}And now full power for the lumpy, bumpy sprint
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.65,0:13:47.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,来到变电站弯\N{\fs90}down to Substation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:49.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,前双闪在大脚刹车后开始亮了起来\N{\fs90}Front hazards coming on under hard braking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.06,0:13:51.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有的菲亚特都这样\N{\fs90}All Fiats do that for some reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.06,0:13:54.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入绵羊坡 反向锁开始工作\N{\fs90}Armful of opposite lock into Field Of Sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.77,0:13:58.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,激情通过 然后冲过终点\N{\fs90}More exuberance through there and across the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.61,0:14:07.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入留你名弯的方式真的很大胆\N{\fs90}It was a ballsy entry into Your Name Here, that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.51,0:14:12.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在让我们看看它能在榜上排在哪儿\N{\fs90}Anyway...we must now find out where it ends up on the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.57,0:14:13.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们来看看\N{\fs90}Let's have a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.02,0:14:17.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦天啊 天啊 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Oh, dear. Oh, dear, Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.45,0:14:18.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你大力推荐了一辆\N{\fs90}So you've recommended what is
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.02,0:14:21.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,被官方证明是世界上最慢的车\N{\fs90}officially the slowest car in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.85,0:14:24.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上 不 只是我们的圈速榜上最慢而已\N{\fs90}Well... No, slowest car on our board.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.93,0:14:26.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们的圈速榜就是世界 -没错\N{\fs90}- Our board is the world. - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.83,0:14:28.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 不过你看 地是湿的\N{\fs90}All right. Look, it was wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.93,0:14:32.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个湖也是湿的 还有人在上面开出过320km/h呢\N{\fs90}That lake's wet. Someone once did 200mph on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.82,0:14:34.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-而且 -我承认 然后他们就死了\N{\fs90}- And... - Then they were killed, I admit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.80,0:14:36.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,-但是 -安静 安静\N{\fs90}- But... - Quite, quite.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.10,0:14:37.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们继续下一个话题 是时候\N{\fs90}Let's move on. It's time now
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.40,0:14:39.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们优雅的航行在\N{\fs90}for us to take a gentle cruise
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.44,0:14:43.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,柔和平静的唠嗑街上了\N{\fs90}down the velvety smoothness of Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.05,0:14:52.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那真的很疼啊 -没错\N{\fs90}- That really hurts. - It did!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.65,0:14:54.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是让你们都清楚这一点\N{\fs90}Just to be absolutely clear with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.79,0:14:56.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,那一下真的 真的很疼\N{\fs90}that really, really hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.56,0:15:01.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 那本来应该是个假瓶子的\N{\fs90}Yeah. It was supposed to be a pretend bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.20,0:15:04.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,-让我们继续 -我想唠点重要的事\N{\fs90}- Let's move it on. - I would like to converse about something important.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.30,0:15:07.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么车上要有真皮座椅\N{\fs90}Why is it that we have leather seats in cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:10.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为实际上 这是一种非常糟糕的材料啊\N{\fs90}Because in reality it's a terrible material.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.37,0:15:11.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,光亮亮滑腻腻\N{\fs90}It's too shiny and slippery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.94,0:15:14.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是太热就是太冷 简直垃圾\N{\fs90}It's too hot or it's too cold. It's rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.11,0:15:16.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得那是因为我们总觉得\N{\fs90}I think it's cos we got hung up on the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.38,0:15:19.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,真皮座椅就象征了豪华\N{\fs90}that leather is somehow posh on a car seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:20.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,但以前并不是这样\N{\fs90}But it didn't use to be like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.98,0:15:22.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,古时候 富贵的人们会坐在\N{\fs90}In the old days, the posh people sat
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.42,0:15:24.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,车后面的真丝座椅上\N{\fs90}in the back of the car on cloth seats,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.55,0:15:26.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,司机坐在前面的真皮座椅上\N{\fs90}and it was the chauffeur sitting at the front--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.32,0:15:27.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为皮椅耐磨\N{\fs90}they gave him leather because it's hard-wearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.99,0:15:30.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,我这里有一张老车的照片\N{\fs90}I've got a picture here of an old car.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.36,0:15:33.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们甚至都没有给他加个车顶挡一下\N{\fs90}They didn't even extend the roof to cover him!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.39,0:15:34.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,只要再长个三英尺就行了啊\N{\fs90}Another three feet would have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.83,0:15:36.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得他们是故意的\N{\fs90}I think that's deliberate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.40,0:15:38.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是为了让司机记得他是个下人\N{\fs90}I think that's to remind him that he's scum!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.33,0:15:43.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了皮子 你们俩想用什么材料做座椅\N{\fs90}What would you two like to have instead of leather?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.07,0:15:44.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,很多东西都能用啊\N{\fs90}There's all sorts of things you could use.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.91,0:15:46.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能用针织毛线\N{\fs90}You could have cable-knit wool.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.91,0:15:51.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,那很棒啊 非常温暖舒适 再让我们四下看看\N{\fs90}But it's nice, it's cosy. Desperately looking around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.18,0:15:54.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他的针织衫拿来做座椅就不错 -温暖舒适\N{\fs90}- His jumper would make quite a good car seat. - Cosy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.08,0:15:56.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是尼龙的 绝对是\N{\fs90}It's nylon! It is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.78,0:15:59.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,再不然就是化纤\N{\fs90}Or pleblon. One of the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.42,0:16:02.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是个好主意啊 -好个鬼啊\N{\fs90}- It's a good idea. - It isn't a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.29,0:16:04.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者这个主意怎么样\N{\fs90}Or, how's this for an idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.43,0:16:06.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就直说吧\N{\fs90}Let me just throw it out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.29,0:16:08.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么不找一头奶牛\N{\fs90}Why not take a cow,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:11.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,把它身上的肉变成汉堡和牛排\N{\fs90}turn the middle of it into burgers and steaks,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.43,0:16:14.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后与其把皮扔掉\N{\fs90}and then, instead of throwing the skin away,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.17,0:16:16.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,不如来做你们车上的座椅\N{\fs90}use it to cover the seats of your car?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.60,0:16:19.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为皮是个很糟糕的材料 根本就不好用啊\N{\fs90}Because it's a terrible material and it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.87,0:16:21.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,那只是因为你们两个\N{\fs90}That's only because you two
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.28,0:16:23.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,决定要开始吃素\N{\fs90}have decided to be vegetarians.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.68,0:16:24.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 等一下...\N{\fs90}Well, no, hang on...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.97,0:16:27.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们真的已经开始吃素了\N{\fs90}They have. They actually have.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.21,0:16:29.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,一天早上他们一起醒来然后决定\N{\fs90}They woke up together one morning and went,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.18,0:16:30.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们不要再吃肉了\N{\fs90}"Let's not eat meat any more."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.48,0:16:33.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们没有从同一张床上醒来过\N{\fs90}We didn't wake up together one morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.69,0:16:35.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-搞明白这一点 -这是个很好的解释啊\N{\fs90}- Get clear on that. - It's a fine definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.59,0:16:38.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,谜一样的在同一天同一个时候\N{\fs90}Mysteriously arrived at the same conclusion
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.69,0:16:39.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,达成了一个共识\N{\fs90}pretty much the same day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:41.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎么说 我们还是要吃鸡肉的\N{\fs90}Anyway, we still eat chicken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.50,0:16:43.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 而且鸡肉属于蔬菜\N{\fs90}Yep. Chicken is a vegetable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.57,0:16:45.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它不是蔬菜 -就是\N{\fs90}- It isn't. - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.63,0:16:48.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,科学的说 鸡确实是蔬菜\N{\fs90}Scientifically, chicken is a vegetable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.37,0:16:51.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你把鸡头砍掉 它还能到处跑\N{\fs90}If you cut a chicken's head off it still runs around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.88,0:16:52.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,说的很对\N{\fs90}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.80,0:16:54.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,那就说明鸡不是有情众生\N{\fs90}Thereby proving it's not a sentient being,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.97,0:16:56.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,它不过是一种高级蔬菜\N{\fs90}it's a higher-order vegetable.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.34,0:16:57.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,很科学的\N{\fs90}Scientifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.64,0:16:59.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 那我们就用鸡皮\N{\fs90}OK, we'll make the seats of your cars
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.65,0:17:02.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,来做你们的座椅 事实上这也不是个坏主意\N{\fs90}out of chicken skins. Actually, that's not a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.15,0:17:06.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,鸡皮座椅看起来会不会很像一个特大号的阴囊\N{\fs90}Wouldn't a chicken-skin seat look like a giant scrotum?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.65,0:17:09.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,会 这都是你们不吃肉的错\N{\fs90}Yes, and that's your fault for not eating meat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.74,0:17:11.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以让我们继续 好吗\N{\fs90}So now let's move on, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.91,0:17:14.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有点话要说 回到上世纪20年代\N{\fs90}I've got something. Back in the 1920s, OK,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.66,0:17:16.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,苏格兰的一个工厂造了一辆汽车\N{\fs90}a Scottish company made a car
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.77,0:17:19.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们说 那是一辆给女士设计的车\N{\fs90}which they said was for women.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.05,0:17:21.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,这有一张照片 它叫Galloway\N{\fs90}Got a picture of it here. It's called the Galloway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.51,0:17:25.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,它凭什么能被称作女性专用\N{\fs90}What about that car makes it for women?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.37,0:17:28.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们说这车的方向盘更小\N{\fs90}Well, they said it had a smaller-than-usual steering wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.41,0:17:31.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,-还有更可靠的引擎 -噢对 当然了\N{\fs90}- and a more reliable engine. - Oh, yeah, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.51,0:17:33.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为男士们可不想要靠谱的引擎 不是吗\N{\fs90}because men don't want a reliable engine, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.85,0:17:35.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,-只有女性想要 -我讨厌靠谱的引擎\N{\fs90}- It's only women! - I hate reliable engines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.35,0:17:36.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,同时 你还能站着开车\N{\fs90}Also, you can drive it standing up,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.98,0:17:39.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,上世纪20年代的女性就是这么开车的\N{\fs90}which is what women did in the 1920s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.19,0:17:40.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这种东西现如今仍在生产\N{\fs90}This sort of thing is still going on today
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.52,0:17:41.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我这有一条新闻说的是\N{\fs90}because I've got news of one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.02,0:17:43.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,西亚特Mii Cosmopolitan\N{\fs90}A car that's been launched
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.65,0:17:46.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,已经开始设计生产了\N{\fs90}called the Seat Mii Cosmopolitan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.39,0:17:48.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们有一张这车的图片 你看\N{\fs90}We have a picture of it. There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.30,0:17:51.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你怎么拼Mii -M-I-I\N{\fs90}- How do you spell Mii? - M-I-I.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:54.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,-实际上是Mii-iii -是Mii-iii\N{\fs90}- It's Mii-iii. - It is Mii-iii.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.30,0:17:57.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有了一辆Mii-iii\N{\fs90}"I've got a Mii-iii."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.54,0:17:59.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车是由西亚特\N{\fs90}It's been done in collaboration
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.40,0:18:00.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,和《时尚》杂志共同推出\N{\fs90}with Cosmopolitan magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.77,0:18:02.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,专为都市女孩设计\N{\fs90}"It's aimed at Cosmo Girl,"it says.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.38,0:18:03.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后 听好了\N{\fs90}And, are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.68,0:18:05.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,拥有眼线般的大灯\N{\fs90}"The headlights have an eyeliner shape."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.51,0:18:08.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,-并不是  -停车更方便\N{\fs90}- No, they don't. -"It's easy to park."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.95,0:18:10.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢是的 因为\N{\fs90}Oh, yeah, cos...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.48,0:18:12.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还是喜欢难停的车\N{\fs90}I much prefer a car that's hard to park
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:14.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我是个男人\N{\fs90}because I'm a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.42,0:18:16.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们能说明一下吗\N{\fs90}Can we get something clear here? OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:19.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,这种分性别的车太荒唐了\N{\fs90}This gender-splitting of cars is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.49,0:18:21.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,就好像是女性飞机座椅\N{\fs90}It's like saying a woman's airline seat
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.66,0:18:24.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者是女性火柴 或者女性任何东西\N{\fs90}or a woman's matches or a woman's anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.90,0:18:27.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能买一盒女性铅笔吗\N{\fs90}"Can I buy a box of women's pencils, please?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.42,0:18:31.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是 我唯一能想到的分性别的东西\N{\fs90}Exactly. The only things I can think of that can be split by gender
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.47,0:18:35.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就是自行车 因为有前梁 -是啊\N{\fs90}- are bicycles, because of the crossbar. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.31,0:18:38.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,-还有内衣 -有时候是的\N{\fs90}- And underwear. - Sometimes, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.55,0:18:42.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,说漏嘴了\N{\fs90}Overshare?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:44.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说出声了\N{\fs90}I said that out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:52.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,当时走得急\N{\fs90}I left in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.23,0:18:54.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,说实话 我无法理解\N{\fs90}Honestly, I just can't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.43,0:18:56.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么人们会觉得有\N{\fs90}why people think there's such a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.48,0:18:58.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,-女性汽车和男性汽车这种东西 -荒谬\N{\fs90}- as a woman's car and a man's car. - Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.67,0:19:00.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,你开车的时候又不是\N{\fs90}It's not as if you drive cars
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.30,0:19:02.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,用你的老兄或者蜜汁三角区开车\N{\fs90}with your old chap or your magic triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.34,0:19:04.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,这儿还有\N{\fs90}And there's um...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.74,0:19:13.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,-听着 -脑补出图像了\N{\fs90}- Listen... - It's a little graphic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.78,0:19:17.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,几年前 沃尔沃做了一款概念车\N{\fs90}But a few years ago, Volvo did a concept car,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:18.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们还大肆吹捧\N{\fs90}and they boasted very loudly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.52,0:19:20.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,说这辆车所有的东西\N{\fs90}that the whole thing had been designed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.49,0:19:22.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是女性设计的\N{\fs90}entirely by women.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.46,0:19:24.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,我这有一张照片\N{\fs90}And I've got a picture of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.56,0:19:26.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一辆有鸥翼门 大功率引擎的轿跑车\N{\fs90}It's a coupe with gull-wing doors and a massive engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.99,0:19:28.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,是个人都这么设计\N{\fs90}It's what everyone would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.33,0:19:30.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我肯定会这么设计的\N{\fs90}I would definitely have done that. Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.26,0:19:31.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,当涉及到汽车的时候\N{\fs90}Men and women are exactly the same
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.50,0:19:33.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,男人和女人完全一样\N{\fs90}when it comes to cars. The end.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.13,0:19:34.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,-正是 -好的 现在\N{\fs90}- Exactly. - Right. Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.37,0:19:35.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道特斯拉吗\N{\fs90}You know Tesla?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.90,0:19:38.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,特斯拉认为它是电动车的先驱者\N{\fs90}Tesla believes it's pioneering the electric car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.97,0:19:41.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,但并不是这样 60年代有个苏格兰公司\N{\fs90}But that ain't so. There was a Scottish company back in the '60s
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.61,0:19:43.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,造了一辆电动车\N{\fs90}which made an electric car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.34,0:19:46.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我这有张照片 -哎我去\N{\fs90}- I've got a picture of it here. -  Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.48,0:19:47.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,它叫做痞子\N{\fs90}It's called The Scamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.05,0:19:50.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,最高时速56公里\N{\fs90}It had a top speed of 35mph,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.98,0:19:52.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,续航里程32公里\N{\fs90}a range of 20 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.69,0:19:55.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想说得非常明白\N{\fs90}And I want to make it absolutely plain,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.16,0:19:56.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是苏格兰的 不是不列颠的\N{\fs90}that's Scottish, not British.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.06,0:20:00.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 毫无疑问\N{\fs90}It is, yes! Very definitely!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.73,0:20:02.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是苏格兰的\N{\fs90}That... that is Scottish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.10,0:20:06.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,唠嗑可以结束了\N{\fs90}We can end the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.60,0:20:09.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在全世界的人\N{\fs90}Now, all over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.40,0:20:12.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,都在买又大又乏味的车\N{\fs90}people, by and large, buy very boring cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.54,0:20:15.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我昨天遇见一个人 他刚花了8000英镑\N{\fs90}I met a man yesterday who'd just spent ￡8,000
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.38,0:20:16.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,买了一辆5年的老福克斯\N{\fs90}on a five-year-old Ford Focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.61,0:20:18.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就想 你图啥呢\N{\fs90}I thought, Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.71,0:20:20.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你有8000英镑预算\N{\fs90}If you've got ￡8,000 to spend,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.38,0:20:23.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,你为什么不买辆二手玛莎拉蒂呢\N{\fs90}why didn't you buy a used Maserati?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.08,0:20:24.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得这是因为 人们相信\N{\fs90}I think it's because people believe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.82,0:20:28.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果花8000英镑买二手的意大利车\N{\fs90}if you buy the used, exotic Italian car for ￡8,000
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.79,0:20:30.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,它肯定不停地坏\N{\fs90}it's going to break down all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.02,0:20:32.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 但真的如此吗 为了找到答案\N{\fs90}Yes, but will it? To find out,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.02,0:20:35.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们用自己的钱\N{\fs90}we actually put our own money on the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.76,0:20:39.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,每人买了一辆二手玛莎拉蒂\N{\fs90}and we each went out and bought a second- hand Maserati.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.94,0:20:42.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 而且我们觉得\N{\fs90}Yes, and then we decided that cars this glamorous
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.80,0:20:46.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样富有激情又迷人的车不能在英国测试\N{\fs90}and this exciting couldn't possibly be tested in Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.77,0:20:51.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们决定在欧洲大陆碰头\N{\fs90}So we decided to meet up in continental Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.65,0:21:02.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我们选的赛道\N{\fs90}This is the race track we selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.62,0:21:05.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,距离加莱只有96公里\N{\fs90}It's just 60 miles from Calais,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.77,0:21:07.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一早就到了 心情愉悦\N{\fs90}and I arrived bright and early.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.94,0:21:18.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一台玛莎拉蒂Biturbo\N{\fs90}This...is a Maserati Biturbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.28,0:21:22.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,世界上第一台装备双涡轮的车\N{\fs90}First car in the world to be fitted with two turbo chargers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.02,0:21:26.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,这台车被命名为S系列\N{\fs90}And this particular example is the sought-after S model.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.88,0:21:30.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且只跑了38000公里\N{\fs90}And it's only done 24,000 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.00,0:21:36.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,尽管如此 我还是花了7950英镑\N{\fs90}And yet despite that, all I paid for it was £7,950.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.42,0:21:40.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,来得到这台魅力十足 马力强劲的车\N{\fs90}So you get all this glamour, all this power,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.86,0:21:44.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有这些车标 而且在英国的价格\N{\fs90}all that badge for less than you'd pay in the UK
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.47,0:21:46.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,比一台六年的丰田普锐斯还便宜\N{\fs90}for a six-year-old Toyota "Pious"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.71,0:21:55.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么哈蒙德开了一台福特Cortina\N{\fs90}Why has Richard Hammond arrived in a Ford Cortina?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.71,0:22:00.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,不对 这不是福特 而是另外一台Biturbo\N{\fs90}Wait. It isn't a Ford Cortina, it's another Biturbo!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.81,0:22:04.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是一台430 -不是\N{\fs90}- No, this is the 430. - It isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.57,0:22:05.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-430 -Biturbo\N{\fs90}- It is! - Biturbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.82,0:22:06.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是Biturbo\N{\fs90}This isn't a Biturbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.00,0:22:08.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,-明明就是 -那才是Biturbo\N{\fs90}- It is! - That's a Biturbo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.74,0:22:09.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.68,0:22:11.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,我很遗憾地告诉你\N{\fs90}I'm sorry to have to tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.20,0:22:13.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是Ghibli Racing \N{\fs90}But the Ghibli, the Racing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.94,0:22:17.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,Karif Shamal 222和430\N{\fs90}the Karif, the Shamal, the 222 and the 430,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.54,0:22:19.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是一样的 根本没钱改\N{\fs90}they were all the same car. They haven't got any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.47,0:22:21.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们只是改了一下尾标\N{\fs90}They just changed the name badge on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.50,0:22:22.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是一样的车\N{\fs90}These are the same car.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.00,0:22:25.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的很丑 但依然是同样的车\N{\fs90}Yours is very ugly, but it's the same car.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.60,0:22:26.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,我反对\N{\fs90}I dispute that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.84,0:22:28.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,这并不是丑 而是优雅\N{\fs90}This is not ugly, this is elegant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.74,0:22:30.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是意大利风格 -才不是呢\N{\fs90}- This is Italian style. - It isn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.00,0:22:33.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一台外观很棒的车子 看啊\N{\fs90}That is a fabulous-looking car. Let's look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.41,0:22:35.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的车子咋样 这很艳俗 伙计\N{\fs90}What have you got? It's a bit gaudy, mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.75,0:22:37.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你想听听这台宝贝点火的声音么\N{\fs90}You wanna hear this baby fire up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.22,0:22:42.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,快出来 逃命啊\N{\fs90}Get out! Save yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.29,0:22:45.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦也\N{\fs90}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.33,0:22:46.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,感受一下这动力吧\N{\fs90}Feel the power of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.05,0:22:48.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看见地上这摊了么\N{\fs90}Have you seen all this--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.60,0:22:50.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了油还能是什么\N{\fs90}there's no other word for it-- oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.60,0:22:52.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs90}Yeah, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.17,0:22:53.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好吧 -好吧\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.27,0:22:54.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,幸运的是\N{\fs90}Happily,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.64,0:22:56.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,在冒出更多的油之前\N{\fs90}before any more could flood out,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.34,0:22:57.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯来了\N{\fs90}James arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.87,0:23:05.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你见过比这货还丑的车子么\N{\fs90}Have you ever seen a more ungainly-looking machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.85,0:23:07.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是怎么了 你的车门坏了么\N{\fs90}What's the matter? Is your door broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.85,0:23:10.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,没 是我坏了 你能帮我扶一下车门么 谢谢\N{\fs90}No, I'm broken. Can you hold the door for me? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.72,0:23:15.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,看啊 这是一台玛莎拉蒂Zagato Spyder\N{\fs90}Behold...the Maserati Zagato Spyder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.97,0:23:18.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,-只是台Biturbo而已 -是Zagato Spyder\N{\fs90}- Biturbo, mate. - Zagato Spyder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.65,0:23:19.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是Biturbo\N{\fs90}All Biturbos.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.40,0:23:21.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想这台车设计于\N{\fs90}I think this was designed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.77,0:23:23.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,公司还属于雪铁龙的时候\N{\fs90}when it was owned by Citroen,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.31,0:23:25.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,当时已经破产了\N{\fs90}which was bankrupt at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.13,0:23:26.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后一些美国人\N{\fs90}Then there was some guy in America
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.80,0:23:28.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,持有了一些玛莎拉蒂的股份\N{\fs90}who had a bit of Maserati.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.22,0:23:30.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后还有意大利政府 或者菲亚特\N{\fs90}And then the Italian Government, or Fiat,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.42,0:23:32.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,都有一点\N{\fs90}they all sort of had bits of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.31,0:23:34.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们到处叫嚣 看啊 我们造了一辆新车 \N{\fs90}They ran around going, We made a new car. Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.81,0:23:37.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,基本一样 只是有了个新名字\N{\fs90}It was exactly the same, it just had a new name.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.68,0:23:40.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好意思 詹姆斯 我只是想看一下\N{\fs90}Excuse me, James. I just want to see just...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.11,0:23:42.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,你还有双色真皮呐\N{\fs90}Oh, you've got two-tone leather.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.88,0:23:45.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过为啥你的是自动挡\N{\fs90}But why have you got an automatic?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.14,0:23:46.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的胳膊断了\N{\fs90}I've bust my arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.65,0:23:48.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么我下车要这么久\N{\fs90}That's why it took a long time to get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.62,0:23:49.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的胳膊真的伤了么\N{\fs90}Have you really broken your arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.86,0:23:51.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,你伤的哪只胳膊\N{\fs90}Which arm have you broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.93,0:23:56.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,这让我杀气腾腾 脾气暴躁\N{\fs90}It has made me murderously bad-tempered
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.42,0:23:58.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,还无法容忍你的愚蠢\N{\fs90}and intolerant of your fatuousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.80,0:24:00.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,你真的伤到胳膊了么\N{\fs90}Have you seriously broken your arm?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.23,0:24:01.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的伤得很严重\N{\fs90}It's fractured quite badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.80,0:24:03.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,-别碰 -你怎么伤的\N{\fs90}- Don't touch it. - How did you break it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.94,0:24:06.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我摔了一跤 -这是你买自动挡的原因吗\N{\fs90}- I fell over. - That's why you got an automatic?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.97,0:24:09.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -车顶是自动的么\N{\fs90}- Yes. - Is that roof electric?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.24,0:24:11.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不是 -这前面有一个按钮\N{\fs90}- No. - There's a button on the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.85,0:24:15.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这样啊 原来是手动的 -是的\N{\fs90}- Oh, right. So it is manual. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.58,0:24:17.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 我们必须出发了 上车走吧\N{\fs90}Anyway, we must get off. Come on, let's drive on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.82,0:24:20.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能帮我把车顶收回来么\N{\fs90}Can you put the roof back up for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.19,0:24:22.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,不能 我才不要\N{\fs90}No! I'm not doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.76,0:24:29.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们决定先进行一场直线加速\N{\fs90}We decided first of all to have a drag race,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.26,0:24:33.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我们的车和另一类价格相当的车\N{\fs90}between our cars and a similarly-priced modern car...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.33,0:24:35.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,铃木"芹菜"之间进行\N{\fs90}the Suzuki Celery.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.11,0:24:41.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,紧张时刻\N{\fs90}Tense moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.88,0:24:52.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,糟糕的是 发车直道太窄了\N{\fs90}Sadly, however, the pit straight was too narrow
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.69,0:24:54.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,无法容纳四台车\N{\fs90}for our four cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.29,0:24:58.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,你弄啥嘞\N{\fs90}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.56,0:25:00.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德你这个白痴\N{\fs90}Hammond, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.83,0:25:07.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你撞了我的玛莎拉蒂 -你撞了我的\N{\fs90}- You crashed into my Maserati! - You crashed into mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.57,0:25:09.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,我无处可去了 那边是护墙\N{\fs90}I've got nowhere to go. There's a barrier there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.77,0:25:12.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也无处可走了 我就在那儿\N{\fs90}There was nowhere for me to go. I was where I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.61,0:25:15.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二次尝试\N{\fs90}So, for the second attempt...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.78,0:25:20.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我主动走了维修道\N{\fs90}I volunteered to go down the pit lane.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.65,0:25:24.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶 我太聪明了\N{\fs90}Yes, this is genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.65,0:25:28.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过这也没有成功\N{\fs90}And that didn't work, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.06,0:25:31.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,重新回到赛道 哈蒙德在那里\N{\fs90}Re-emerging on the track. Hammond is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.97,0:25:33.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,搞什么鬼\N{\fs90}What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.22,0:25:35.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,糟糕\N{\fs90}Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.06,0:25:38.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天呐\N{\fs90}Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.87,0:25:44.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么我们不能好好跑一场加速赛\N{\fs90}Why the hell can't we just do a drag race properly?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.60,0:25:46.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,能有什么难的\N{\fs90}It can't be that difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.61,0:25:49.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,又经历了一次事故后 我们决定\N{\fs90}After this latest accident, we decided that,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.84,0:25:53.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,由于哈蒙德的车子排量最大\N{\fs90}as Hammond's car had the biggest engine...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.45,0:25:56.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,由他来代表玛莎拉蒂的荣耀出战\N{\fs90}he'd represent Maserati's honour on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.95,0:26:01.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 就是这样了 我是被选中的车手\N{\fs90}OK, this is it. I am the elected driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.36,0:26:05.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,天选之子 自带主角光环\N{\fs90}The chosen one. The kingpin.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.49,0:26:08.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,我很喜欢\N{\fs90}I like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.30,0:26:15.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,轮胎溅起了大量的水\N{\fs90}Massive amount of bleeping about...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.27,0:26:19.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过\N{\fs90}But then...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.07,0:26:24.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,终于 涡轮开始发力\N{\fs90}Finally, it spools up, turbos whizzing away.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.51,0:26:30.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,绝对碾压\N{\fs90}And yes! Absolutely creamed it!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.09,0:26:34.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们选择我实在是太正确了\N{\fs90}Yep, they were right to pick me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.06,0:26:38.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有这台车 玛莎拉蒂 430\N{\fs90}And the car, the 430...Maserati.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.06,0:26:42.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在你已经证明了 作为一个团队\N{\fs90}Now you've established that, as a team,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.80,0:26:45.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们的双涡轮增压玛莎拉蒂比\N{\fs90}our twin turbo-charged Maseratis are faster
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.43,0:26:47.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,67马力的小铃木快多了\N{\fs90}than a 67-horsepower Celery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.77,0:26:50.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在让我们抛开这台小车\N{\fs90}let's get rid of the little Japanese car
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.34,0:26:53.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,来看一下我们这三台车里\N{\fs90}and find out which of our three cars
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.81,0:26:56.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,哪一个在这条赛道跑的最快\N{\fs90}is the fastest round the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.08,0:26:57.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们将会驾驶着玛莎拉蒂\N{\fs90}We'll be driving Maseratis
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.01,0:27:00.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,狂奔在欧洲大陆的赛道上\N{\fs90}on a race track in continental Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.58,0:27:02.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,听起来很棒不是么\N{\fs90}Sounds good, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.28,0:27:04.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,你怎么了 怎么看起来如此悲惨\N{\fs90}What's the matter with you? Why do you look so miserable?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.99,0:27:08.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的胳膊断了\N{\fs90}I've broken my arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.06,0:27:10.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我们要跑赛道的话\N{\fs90}If we're gonna drive round a track,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.69,0:27:13.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,至少能给我一个残疾人用的方向盘助力球吗\N{\fs90}can I at least have one of those disabled knob things?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.99,0:27:16.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你懂的 -就是方向盘上的那种\N{\fs90}- You know. - On the steering wheel?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.82,0:27:18.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 就像叉车上的那样\N{\fs90}Yeah, like a forklift truck has.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.08,0:27:18.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,听起来相当公平啊\N{\fs90}Sounds fair enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.27,0:27:23.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在我们的同事享受\N{\fs90}So, whilst our colleague enjoyed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.37,0:27:25.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的特殊早餐的时候\N{\fs90}his special breakfast,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.81,0:27:28.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德和我安装好了他的助力球\N{\fs90}Richard and I attached his steering knob.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.24,0:27:29.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,走你\N{\fs90}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.74,0:27:32.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后我们驶上了赛道\N{\fs90}And then we hit the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.51,0:27:36.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,这台车的起源\N{\fs90}The roots of this car,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.38,0:27:41.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,是1957年的 德国大奖赛\N{\fs90}they were planted during the 1957 German Grand Prix.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.09,0:27:44.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,方吉奥驾驶的那台玛莎拉蒂250F\N{\fs90}Fangio, at the wheel of his Maserati 250F,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.39,0:27:50.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,他在22圈里追上了48秒的差距 赢得了比赛\N{\fs90}overcame a 48-second deficit in 22 laps to win the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.96,0:27:54.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,期间十次打破圈速记录\N{\fs90}He smashed the lap record ten times.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.13,0:27:58.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样的家族血统是不会轻易消失的\N{\fs90}You don't lose a pedigree like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.44,0:28:01.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,走你 感觉尾巴有点躁动\N{\fs90}Here we go. Feel the tail kick out a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.58,0:28:04.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者前面也有点\N{\fs90}Or the front go.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.64,0:28:06.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,还是车尾 又到前面\N{\fs90}There's the back. On the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.48,0:28:10.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊 我控制住了\N{\fs90}Oh, God. I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.92,0:28:17.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,驾驶玛莎拉蒂进行飞驰圈\N{\fs90}Flying laps in a Maserati.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.12,0:28:19.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就和斯特灵莫斯做的一样\N{\fs90}This is exactly what Stirling Moss did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.57,0:28:29.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,并不完全一样 有一点像\N{\fs90}Not exactly. Bits of it are.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.77,0:28:32.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,与此同时 在敞篷车里\N{\fs90}Meanwhile, in the convertible,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.84,0:28:36.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯对于自己的新方向盘旋钮很不满意\N{\fs90}James was very unhappy with his new steering knob.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.78,0:28:44.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊 这是个左手弯\N{\fs90}Oh, God, it's the left-hander.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.79,0:28:49.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,把儿都弯了\N{\fs90}Bend the knob.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.99,0:28:52.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,那两个家伙有什么毛病\N{\fs90}What is the matter with those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.93,0:28:58.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们很好 我们状态很棒\N{\fs90}We're OK. We're in good shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.90,0:29:02.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我们没有\N{\fs90}- No, we're not!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.50,0:29:04.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,尽管我幸运地救回了车\N{\fs90}Despite my lucky-dip handling,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.54,0:29:06.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,我最终还是赶上了哈蒙德\N{\fs90}I did eventually catch Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.18,0:29:12.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,超他 就在内线超\N{\fs90}Take him! Take him on the inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.11,0:29:13.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶\N{\fs90}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.71,0:29:16.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶\N{\fs90}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.32,0:29:19.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要啊\N{\fs90}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.83,0:29:27.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要啊 我的天啊\N{\fs90}No, I... Oh, God, strewth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.53,0:29:31.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就像要失控了\N{\fs90}He's going surely now!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.83,0:29:33.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊\N{\fs90}Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.70,0:29:40.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,这台车的马力太大了 加油啊\N{\fs90}It just has too many horsepowers here. Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.94,0:29:44.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,糟糕\N{\fs90}Oh, shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.21,0:29:50.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,克拉克森先生的情况有些不妙\N{\fs90}Mr Clarkson is indisposed briefly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.58,0:29:54.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,过了一会儿 哈蒙德先生也没有幸免\N{\fs90}And moments later, so was Mr Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.62,0:29:56.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要啊\N{\fs90}No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.62,0:29:59.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,给点力啊\N{\fs90}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.66,0:30:04.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有得出任何结论之后\N{\fs90}So, having learned absolutely nothing at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.30,0:30:07.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们决定不跑赛道了\N{\fs90}we decided to abandon the race track
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.20,0:30:09.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,而是进行一次1100公里的巡游\N{\fs90}and embark on a 700-mile cruise
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.80,0:30:12.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,前往法国南部\N{\fs90}to the south of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.57,0:30:16.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯对于这项计划感到很开心\N{\fs90}James was very pleased with this plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.11,0:30:18.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,这才像样嘛 不是么\N{\fs90}This is more like it, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.21,0:30:19.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要在赛道上乱跑\N{\fs90}Not mucking around on a race track,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.88,0:30:22.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,那样的坏主意不适合这些老车\N{\fs90}which is always a bad idea in old cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.08,0:30:24.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要进行一次像样的公路旅行\N{\fs90}We're going on a proper road trip
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.08,0:30:25.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,去世界上最可爱的地方\N{\fs90}to a lovely part of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.92,0:30:29.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,驾驶着令人回味而有异国情调的\N{\fs90}in very, very evocative, exotic cars--
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.72,0:30:31.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,玛莎拉蒂\N{\fs90}Maserati!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.93,0:30:35.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,在20世纪70年代 玛莎拉蒂把全部车型都以\N{\fs90}In the 1970s, Maserati was naming all its cars
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.88,0:30:39.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,充满异域风情的暖流来命名\N{\fs90}after...exotic-sounding warm winds:
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.20,0:30:42.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如Mistral Khamsin Bora\N{\fs90}Mistral, Khamsin, Bora.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.30,0:30:46.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,当我在唐卡斯特度过童年时光的时候\N{\fs90}When I was a kid growing up in Doncaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.01,0:30:48.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就想\N{\fs90}I just thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.21,0:30:50.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不知道Mistral是啥\N{\fs90}I've no idea what a Mistral is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.38,0:30:51.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我就想要一个\N{\fs90}but I want one!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.25,0:30:56.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,玛莎拉蒂  法国南部\N{\fs90}Maserati. South of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.22,0:30:59.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,一切都是那么合拍\N{\fs90}It just sounds right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.59,0:31:03.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是很快\N{\fs90}However, fairly soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.46,0:31:06.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,现实开始变得\N{\fs90}reality began to stick its unwelcome nose
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.66,0:31:08.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,异常残酷\N{\fs90}into the equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.39,0:31:12.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车没有暖风 我也没办法除雾\N{\fs90}You get no heat in here and I can't de-mist at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.93,0:31:14.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有刹车\N{\fs90}The brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.94,0:31:16.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一边刹车很好\N{\fs90}It brakes one wheel very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.70,0:31:20.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是每次都只有一边有刹车 还不知道是哪一边\N{\fs90}But only one wheel at a time. And you never know which one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.98,0:31:26.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 我的车灯晃到你了么\N{\fs90}James, are my lights dazzling you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.58,0:31:31.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一点 因为我开的是大灯\N{\fs90}- Yeah, a bit. - Because they seem to be on main beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.94,0:31:32.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我没法调成近光\N{\fs90}but I can't dip them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.02,0:31:35.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,有趣的是 就算我开远光灯\N{\fs90}Interesting thing is,if I put my headlights on full beam,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.49,0:31:37.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,对向也没人对我闪灯啊\N{\fs90}nobody coming the other way flashes at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.73,0:31:43.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,你听到那个响声了么\N{\fs90}You hear that rattling?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.80,0:31:45.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,是方向盘\N{\fs90}That's the steering wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.47,0:31:49.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了车子本身的问题外\N{\fs90}On top of the mechanical issues,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.97,0:31:51.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有一个问题\N{\fs90}there was the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.37,0:31:53.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是詹姆斯在右舵车里\N{\fs90}of James tackling the toll booths
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.17,0:31:55.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,试图缴过路费\N{\fs90}in his right-hand-drive car.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.32,0:32:11.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们还剩1126公里\N{\fs90}We've got 700 miles to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.60,0:32:15.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,按这速度 永远都开不到了\N{\fs90}It's going to take us for ever at this speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.36,0:32:18.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,雪上加霜的是\N{\fs90}And then, to cap it all...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.68,0:32:22.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 你车底火花四射\N{\fs90}Jeremy, there are sparks coming from under your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.00,0:32:26.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得你得停车看看\N{\fs90}I think you probably need to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.57,0:32:30.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,-快看  -什么东西起火了\N{\fs90}- Oh, look. - Something's on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.94,0:32:33.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,-起火啦  -嗯 撒泡尿灭火吧\N{\fs90}-Fire!  -Right. Might have to piss on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.77,0:32:36.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-别啊  -你先回避\N{\fs90}- Oh, no! - Go round there!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.77,0:32:41.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,他肯定会解释这是紧急服务\N{\fs90}He's going to claim to be an emergency service now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.32,0:32:43.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,可惜 我们的旅程\N{\fs90}Annoyingly, our road trip
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.57,0:32:46.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,不如想象的那般入流\N{\fs90}wasn't proving to be as stylish as we'd hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.39,0:32:50.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,在下一个加油点\N{\fs90}So, at the next petrol stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.40,0:32:52.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯对我们买的礼物\N{\fs90}with James failing to appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.51,0:32:54.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,欣赏无能\N{\fs90}a present we'd bought for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.31,0:32:55.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,你以前幽默感很好的\N{\fs90}You used to have a good sense of humour.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.80,0:32:58.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在搞笑的时候 我确实能配合\N{\fs90}I do have a good sense of humour when you're being funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.44,0:33:00.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,-但很难得  -我有个新主意\N{\fs90}- Which you are sometimes. - ...I suggested a new idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.91,0:33:03.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,听下我的新想法\N{\fs90}Listen, listen. I've had a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.37,0:33:04.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,法国南部太远了\N{\fs90}South of France is a long way away.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.91,0:33:08.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们干嘛不去法国北部\N{\fs90}So why don't we go to the north of France instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.48,0:33:10.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-有道理  -好主意\N{\fs90}- Yes! - That is a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.58,0:33:12.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,比起南部\N{\fs90}And there's much more to see and do in the north
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.05,0:33:15.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,北部更好看 更好玩\N{\fs90}than there is in the south of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.39,0:33:17.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,北部有什么好看的\N{\fs90}What is there to see and do in the north of France?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.82,0:33:21.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,加莱有个难民营\N{\fs90}Well, there's the immigrant camp in Calais.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.40,0:33:24.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有那个烧死女人的广场\N{\fs90}There's that square where they set fire to a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.77,0:33:26.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有呢\N{\fs90}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.37,0:33:36.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,肯定还有其他玩意儿的\N{\fs90}There'll be other stuff. There will be other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.08,0:33:41.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢各位\N{\fs90}OK. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.82,0:33:46.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you so much. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.19,0:33:48.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们稍后再继续\N{\fs90}We'll pick that up later on,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.14,0:33:51.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,但现在又到了明星脑碰脑环节\N{\fs90}but now it's time to play Celebrity Brain Crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.13,0:34:02.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,-依然糟糕  -不忍直视\N{\fs90}- Yeah, it's still terrible. - Awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.10,0:34:07.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 对于本周的嘉宾有什么可说的呢\N{\fs90}OK, now what can we say about our guest this week?
